Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce. Peel and dice @sweet potatoes{2} into ½-inch pieces. Trim and halve
@zucchini{1} lengthwise; slice crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Zest
and halve @lemon{1}.

Place sweet potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by
2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Drain and
return sweet potatoes to pot. Mash with @sour cream{2%tablespoon} and
@butter{1%tablespoon}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Keep covered off
heat.

> If you like your sweet potatoes extra sweet, add ½ tsp sugar for 2 or 1 tsp
> for 4 while mashing.

Meanwhile, toss zucchini on a #baking sheet{} with lemon zest, a drizzle of
@olive oil{2%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. Place lemon halves cut sides down
on same sheet. Roast on top rack, flipping zucchini halfway through, until
browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}. Tent with #foil{} to keep warm.

> Start with half, taste, and add more roasted lemon juice from there if desired.

Meanwhile, pat @pork chops{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; prick all over
with a fork or knife. Season all over with @garlic powder{1%teaspoon},
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through,
~{4-6%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

> If pork begins to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium.

Return same pan to medium-high heat. Add @chicken stock concentrate{1} and
¼ cup water. Simmer until slightly reduced, ~{2-4%minutes}. Add any resting
juices from pork. Remove from heat and stir in @garlic herb butter{2%tablespoon}.

> If sauce is too thick, stir in a splash of water.

Toss zucchini with as much roasted lemon juice as you like. Divide between
plates with sweet potatoes and pork. Top pork with pan sauce.